        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 7:59PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 759 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 6
miles southwest of Lockesburg, or 6 miles east of Horatio, moving
southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Lockesburg, Ben Lomond, Oak Grove, Bellview and Central.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
